  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Inclusive Education for the States of Tamilnadu</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of this Inclusive Education Project is to provide quality education for disabled children in Tamil Nadu.
The main activities of this Inclusive education project are:
&#x2022; To provide eye screening for children enrolled in government schools among the seven districts (Villupuram, Salem, Nilgiris, Namakkal, Theni, Ramnathpuram and Madurai).
&#x2022; Provide appropriate treatment for children that are identified as being visually impaired
&#x2022; Providing training for Inclusive education teachers
&#x2022; Providing teachers with training on undertaking refractive screening
This Inclusive education project is being implemented with a purpose to ensure that the government of Tamil Nadu provides quality education services with support services within the wider education system for Visually Impaired children by strengthening the Inclusive Education model by 2015</narrative>
  </description>
